Thailand Stocks: Banpu, Central Pattana, Khon Kaen Sugar, PTT

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-08-30T10:09:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/thailand-stocks-khon-kaen-sugar-ptt-exploration-thai-rubber.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index fell 10.66 points, or 1 percent, to 1,044.97,
the first decline in three days.  Energy companies:  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s biggest oil
company, dropped 2.1 percent to 322 baht, the most since Aug.
19.  Banpu Pcl (BANPU)  , the nation’s biggest coal producer,
lost 1.9 percent to 618 baht, the first decrease in three days.  Brent crude  fell from near its highest in three weeks in
 London  on speculation that stockpiles are increasing in the
U.S., the biggest consumer of the commodity.  Central Pattana Pcl (CPN)  , Thailand’s largest shopping
mall developer, advanced 1.4 percent to 36.75 baht. The company
plans to spend 53.7 billion baht ($1.8 billion) over the next
five years to develop new projects. The company’s annual revenue
will grow about 15 percent through 2015 as it opens new shopping
centers and renovates existing malls, Chief Financial Officer
Naris Cheyklin said at a briefing in Bangkok today.  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)  , a sugar producer,
climbed 1.4 percent to 14.30 baht. Asia Plus Securities Pcl
raised the share-price estimate for Khon Kaen by 19 percent to
19.90 baht, citing an increase in overseas shipments and prices.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
